State Metric Ranker

Rank states by a metric for a given year

Metric:

Notes
  • Margin: difference between Democratic and Republican vote share (D − R). Displayed as e.g. D+5.2.
  • Two-party: excludes third-party votes and recalculates margins on a D vs R two-party basis.
  • Relative: the state's margin minus the national margin.
  • Delta: change in the chosen metric since the previous election.
